Exercise 5-15
Add the option -f to fold upper and lower case together, so that case distinctions are not made during sorting; for example, 'a' and 'A' compare equal.

Brief explanation:
--
For a generic explanation of the approach taken, please refer to the readme file of exercise 5-14.
Assuming you've read it, this is really simple. We will use strcasecmp, part of string.h, to make the case insensitive comparison. When we read -f, we change the order function to a wrapper 
for strcasecmp.


GCC command:
gcc -o solution solution.c -Wall
